{{Chinese||s=谭栖伟 |t=譚棲偉 |p=Tán Qīweǐ }}

'''Tan Qiwei''' (born August 1954) is a Chinese politician of [[Tujia people|Tujia]] ethnic heritage.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.npc.gov.cn/englishnpc/news/2011-03/10/content_1640132.htm |title=Notice No.30 Vice Mayor Tan Qiwei of Chongqing takes interview |date= 2011-03-10 |publisher=National People's Congress }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://en.cq.gov.cn/ChongqingToday/Headlines/2012/4/1/983532.shtml |title=Collection of RMB 5 Billion Overseas Fund in 3 Years for Developing Chongqing Tourism |date=2012-04-01 |publisher= |work= }}</ref> He was the Vice Mayor of Chongqing, then the Vice Chairman of the Chongqing People's Congress. He was dismissed from office in May 2014 and placed under investigation by the Communist Party's anti-corruption body.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.chinatourism.ch/html/2009/Travel_0422/171.html |title=Domestic Tourism Trade Fair 2009 Successfully Concluded |date=15 April 2009 |publisher= |work=chinatourism.ch }}</ref>

==Biography==
Tan was born and raised in [[Shizhu County]], [[Chongqing]], where he graduated from [[Central Party School of the Communist Party of China|Chongqing Party School of the Communist Party of China]].

Tan joined the workforce in March 1973 and joined the [[Communist Party of China]] in November 1973.

During the [[Cultural Revolution]], Tan worked as a [[sent-down youth]] in his hometown.

In July 1985, he was appointed the CPC County Committee Vice-Secretary and County Governor of [[Shizhu Tujia Autonomous County]], he remained in that position until September 1989, when he was transferred to [[Youyang Tujia and Miao Autonomous County]] and appointed the CPC County Committee Secretary.

From November 1991 to March 1997, Tan worked in [[Qianjiang District]] of Chongqing as an officer. Then he was transferred to [[Nan'an District]] as the District Mayor and CPC Vice-Secretary, he became the CPC Party Secretary in December 2001, and served until March 2006.

In March 2006 he was promoted to become the [[Politics of Chongqing|Vice Mayor of Chongqing]], a position he held until January 2013, he took charge of the project [[Three Gorges Dam]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://news.163.com/14/0504/02/9RC9P42O00014AEE.html |script-title=zh:重庆人大常委会副主任被查 或因三峡移民工作 |date=2014-05-04 |publisher=163.COM |work= |language= zh}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://leaders.people.com.cn/n/2014/0504/c58278-24968910.html |script-title=zh:重庆人大副主任谭栖伟系今年第7位落马省部级地方官 |date=2014-05-04 |publisher= |work=people.com.cn |language= zh}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://news.qq.com/a/20140504/002198.htm |script-title=zh:重庆人大副主任谭栖伟被调查 上月曾密集亮相 |date=2014-05-04 |publisher= |work=qq.com|language=zh }}</ref> In January 2013, Tan was appointed as the Vice-Chairman of [[National People's Congress|Chongqing People's Congress]].

On May 3, 2014, Tan was being investigated by the [[Central Commission for Discipline Inspection of the Communist Party of China|Party's internal disciplinary body]] for "serious violations of laws and regulations".<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.breakingnews.com/item/2014/05/03/tan-qiwei-vice-director-of-standing-committee-of/ |title=Tan Qiwei, Vice Director of Standing Committee of Chongqing Municipal People's Congress, under investigation for violation of laws. |date=2014-05-03 |publisher= |work= }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.wantinews.com/news-8248870-Chongqing-People-39s-Congress-deputy-director-Tan-Qiwei-checked-suspected-serious-violation-of-law-was-the-deputy-mayor-of-Chongqing-Municipal-Government.html |title=Chongqing People's Congress deputy director Tan Qiwei checked suspected serious violation of law was the deputy mayor of Chongqing Municipal Government |date=2014-05-04 |publisher= |work= }}</ref> Tan was removed from office in September 2014, and expelled from the Communist Party of China.<ref>{{cite news|script-title=zh:重庆市人大常委会原副主任谭栖伟被"双开"|url=http://www.ccdi.gov.cn/ajcc/201409/t20140902_27073.html|date=2014-09-15|work=CDIC|language=zh}}</ref>

On January 7, 2016, Tan was sentenced to 12-year jail and confiscate personal property worth 1 million yuan (~$154,000) for taking bribes worth 11 million yuan by the court.<ref>{{cite web |url = http://www.chinacourt.org/article/detail/2016/01/id/1783870.shtml |script-title=zh:重庆市人大原副主任谭栖伟受贿1143万获刑12年|language=zh |date =January 7, 2016|work= Chinacourt.org}}</ref>

